WEBVTT

00:00:50.154 --> 00:00:52.574
ALL FIGURES, INCIDENTS, LOCATIONS,
ORGANIZATIONS, AND OTHERS ARE FICTITIOUS

00:00:52.657 --> 00:00:55.076
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS WERE FILMED
SAFELY IN ACCORDANCE WITH GUIDELINES

00:00:56.828 --> 00:01:01.833
{\an8}EPISODE 2

00:01:03.084 --> 00:01:05.712
He suddenly started
talking nonsense like a madman.

00:01:05.795 --> 00:01:07.589
He tumbled down and bumped his head.

00:01:07.672 --> 00:01:09.799
Then, he sprawled on the floor
and blacked out--

00:01:09.883 --> 00:01:11.718
Oh, I-rang. Are you okay?

00:01:11.801 --> 00:01:13.178
Do you recognize me? Who am I?

00:01:13.261 --> 00:01:14.345
Yes, what is it?

00:01:15.263 --> 00:01:16.264
Bong-su.

00:01:16.347 --> 00:01:18.349
I'm okay, so tell them to drop us off.

00:01:18.433 --> 00:01:21.519
No, you're not okay.
You asked for an ambulance earlier.

00:01:22.020 --> 00:01:24.063
That was because I felt
too ashamed to stay there.

00:01:32.530 --> 00:01:33.740
{\an8}Goodbye.

00:01:34.866 --> 00:01:36.576
{\an8}I-rang, wait for me.

00:01:36.659 --> 00:01:38.369
{\an8}I really don't get it, though.

00:01:38.453 --> 00:01:40.121
{\an8}You're all good after tumbling that hard?

00:01:40.204 --> 00:01:42.457
{\an8}- Then, was it all an act?
- An act?

00:01:42.540 --> 00:01:45.710
{\an8}You suddenly swore in dialect,
pointed your finger at the defendant,

00:01:45.793 --> 00:01:47.128
{\an8}and even tried to attack him.

00:01:47.211 --> 00:01:48.213
{\an8}I did that?

00:01:48.796 --> 00:01:50.423
Yes, you did.

00:01:50.506 --> 00:01:52.425
You should be nominated for an Oscar.

00:01:52.508 --> 00:01:55.178
It wasn't an act! I blacked out for real.

00:01:56.304 --> 00:01:58.723
Wait. Where are you going in that state?

00:01:58.806 --> 00:01:59.974
- My office.
- What?

00:02:00.058 --> 00:02:02.185
I can't go on like this.
I need to put an end to it.

00:02:02.268 --> 00:02:03.519
An end?

00:02:05.521 --> 00:02:07.440
Hello, Father. This is Shin I-rang.

00:02:07.523 --> 00:02:09.901
I'm sorry, but could you
come over to my office?

00:02:09.984 --> 00:02:11.569
Yes, this is an emergency.

00:02:12.237 --> 00:02:13.238
What…

00:02:19.327 --> 00:02:20.536
Hello, Mother.

00:02:20.620 --> 00:02:21.996
Did you arrive?

00:02:22.080 --> 00:02:23.081
Which hospital is it?

00:02:23.873 --> 00:02:25.083
Oh, the thing is…

00:02:26.334 --> 00:02:29.212
He went to his office just fine.
I don't think you should worry.

00:02:29.837 --> 00:02:31.005
Where is his office?

00:02:32.340 --> 00:02:33.341
That,

00:02:34.259 --> 00:02:35.343
I don't know.

00:02:38.680 --> 00:02:39.722
{\an8}Which hospital is it?

00:02:39.806 --> 00:02:42.058
{\an8}COURTROOMS,
CIVIL MEDIATION CENTER, ANNEX

00:02:42.141 --> 00:02:44.936
- He went to his office.
- He did?

00:02:46.646 --> 00:02:48.356
That means he's not injured much.

00:02:48.856 --> 00:02:50.400
What a relief.

00:02:50.483 --> 00:02:54.153
Did I-rang give you his business card?

00:02:54.237 --> 00:02:55.113
What?

00:02:55.196 --> 00:02:56.823
No, he said he didn't have any yet.

00:02:59.659 --> 00:03:01.202
Oh, excuse me.

00:03:03.454 --> 00:03:05.832
I'm Attorney Shin I-rang's family.

00:03:06.541 --> 00:03:10.086
Do you perhaps know where his office is?

00:03:10.753 --> 00:03:11.754
I do.

00:03:13.798 --> 00:03:14.799
Here you go.

00:03:15.383 --> 00:03:16.384
Thank you.

00:03:17.719 --> 00:03:19.846
PRINCIPAL ATTORNEY SHIN I-RANG

00:03:22.140 --> 00:03:23.433
Okcheon Building?

00:03:29.981 --> 00:03:31.691
Shin I-rang is a total nutcase.

00:03:32.233 --> 00:03:33.568
We might win easily thanks to him.

00:03:37.739 --> 00:03:38.740
Prosecutor Kim?

00:03:39.532 --> 00:03:40.867
Long time no see, Na-hyun.

00:03:40.950 --> 00:03:43.328
What brings you to a civil trial,
Prosecutor Kim?

00:03:43.411 --> 00:03:46.080
I decided to stop by
because I was curious.

00:03:46.164 --> 00:03:47.290
What?

00:03:47.373 --> 00:03:48.499
A search and seizure?

00:03:51.252 --> 00:03:53.296
Okay. I'll be there soon.

00:03:55.340 --> 00:03:57.467
Are you raiding Cheongil Hospital?

00:03:58.217 --> 00:03:59.302
There's no reason to do so.

00:03:59.385 --> 00:04:00.636
A man died.

00:04:01.346 --> 00:04:03.848
An investigation will determine
whether there's a reason or not.

00:04:05.183 --> 00:04:06.184
See you again, Na-hyun.

00:04:11.689 --> 00:04:14.192
That darn prosecutor is
just as annoying as ever.

00:04:16.611 --> 00:04:18.404
I better try
persuading the plaintiff again.

00:04:18.488 --> 00:04:21.699
She shouldn't act recklessly
at least for her sick daughter.

00:04:28.581 --> 00:04:29.749
Is what I asked for ready?

00:04:30.375 --> 00:04:31.376
Yes, sir.

00:04:33.044 --> 00:04:35.546
GANGSTER PATIENT WHO ASSAULTED
MEDICAL STAFF FALSELY CLAIMS MALPRACTICE

00:04:36.589 --> 00:04:38.591
Let's seal the deal
while we have the upper hand.

00:04:38.674 --> 00:04:41.135
Send this to the reporters
and plant it among YouTubers.

00:04:41.886 --> 00:04:42.887
Yes, sir.

00:04:50.603 --> 00:04:52.563
I should've burned these from the start.

00:04:52.647 --> 00:04:54.816
This happened because I was such a softie.

00:04:57.068 --> 00:04:59.070
I know it's not my business,

00:04:59.153 --> 00:05:00.780
but what about the case?

00:05:02.031 --> 00:05:03.199
I'll continue on my own.

00:05:04.575 --> 00:05:06.160
I'd like you to pray for him

00:05:06.869 --> 00:05:08.788
so that he can rest in peace at least.

00:05:09.539 --> 00:05:11.916
Why don't we wait until he comes

00:05:11.999 --> 00:05:13.584
for the sake of your time together?

00:05:14.210 --> 00:05:17.296
I might be swayed if I see him.

00:05:18.131 --> 00:05:19.298
Are you sure about this?

00:05:21.426 --> 00:05:22.635
Let me do it myself.

00:05:34.897 --> 00:05:36.399
GANGSTER PATIENT WHO ASSAULTED
MEDICAL STAFF FALSELY CLAIMS MALPRACTICE

00:05:48.911 --> 00:05:50.746
WHAT WOULD YOU EXPECT
FROM A GANGSTER? LOL

00:05:50.830 --> 00:05:53.416
JI-WOO

00:06:09.640 --> 00:06:10.725
What the…

00:06:14.103 --> 00:06:15.271
Ji-woo!

00:06:16.564 --> 00:06:18.482
What's going on? What's wrong?

00:06:21.402 --> 00:06:24.280
SCUM IS BETTER OFF DEAD,
JUSTICE SERVED, NICE!

00:06:30.494 --> 00:06:31.495
Darn it.

00:06:43.633 --> 00:06:45.134
Leave the rest to me…

00:06:47.261 --> 00:06:48.262
and rest in peace.

00:06:53.726 --> 00:06:56.062
No! Not now!

00:07:17.166 --> 00:07:18.626
Mr. Shin?

00:07:19.752 --> 00:07:21.671
You anchovy head.

00:07:23.339 --> 00:07:25.216
Stop right this instant.

00:07:25.299 --> 00:07:27.885
You know nothing!
Who are you to meddle with it?

00:07:48.781 --> 00:07:50.199
I need to go to my daughter.

00:07:51.117 --> 00:07:53.494
Don't try to get in the way,
or I'll make you pay.

00:07:55.580 --> 00:07:57.498
How could you do this to the priest!

00:08:01.043 --> 00:08:04.005
Did you just hit me, lady?

00:08:04.589 --> 00:08:06.549
What? "Lady"?

00:08:07.717 --> 00:08:10.595
I worked my butt off
to raise and educate you,

00:08:10.678 --> 00:08:13.472
and you dare call me "lady"?

00:08:15.558 --> 00:08:16.684
Say that again.

00:08:16.767 --> 00:08:18.978
Say that again, brat.

00:08:19.812 --> 00:08:21.188
Run away.

00:08:21.772 --> 00:08:24.483
This man isn't your son.

00:08:24.567 --> 00:08:26.068
What?

00:08:33.534 --> 00:08:34.785
Shin I-rang!

00:08:53.638 --> 00:08:55.097
What…

00:08:55.181 --> 00:08:56.557
What is going on?

00:09:01.187 --> 00:09:02.188
Ji-woo.

00:09:07.777 --> 00:09:09.195
Ji-woo…

00:09:14.825 --> 00:09:15.868
So, are you saying

00:09:16.452 --> 00:09:19.288
that this talisman summoned a ghost,

00:09:20.289 --> 00:09:24.251
my son happened to see that ghost
after opening his law office here,

00:09:24.335 --> 00:09:28.214
and that very ghost is
the victim of the earlier trial,

00:09:28.297 --> 00:09:29.382
Lee Gang-pung?

00:09:30.341 --> 00:09:31.342
That's right.

00:09:37.932 --> 00:09:41.560
Will I-rang come back
if we burn this talisman to ashes?

00:09:42.144 --> 00:09:43.145
Not now.

00:09:43.896 --> 00:09:45.272
He's possessed at the moment,

00:09:45.356 --> 00:09:48.192
so we don't know
what will happen if we do.

00:09:51.153 --> 00:09:53.447
LEE GANG-PUNG

00:10:01.372 --> 00:10:02.998
What happened?

00:10:09.171 --> 00:10:10.464
Help me, Mr. Attorney.

00:10:10.548 --> 00:10:11.590
I don't want to.

00:10:11.674 --> 00:10:14.427
I get that you're a ghost,
but have some shame.

00:10:14.510 --> 00:10:16.470
After all that you did,
you want my help again?

00:10:17.138 --> 00:10:18.431
This will be the last time.

00:10:18.514 --> 00:10:19.849
Go away.

00:10:19.932 --> 00:10:22.143
You just wouldn't listen
when I talk to you nicely.

00:10:23.602 --> 00:10:24.603
Ji-woo is sick!

00:10:34.655 --> 00:10:36.240
She read that article about my past.

00:10:37.408 --> 00:10:38.409
It must've shocked her.

00:10:39.535 --> 00:10:42.830
She clutched her stomach in pain
and passed out.

00:10:42.913 --> 00:10:45.499
Why did you save it until now?
You should've told me right away!

00:10:47.585 --> 00:10:48.711
Geez.

00:10:55.009 --> 00:10:56.218
Darn it.

00:11:07.480 --> 00:11:08.689
Can you take me to Sadang-dong?

00:11:08.773 --> 00:11:10.191
- Sure, get in.
- Okay.

00:11:14.528 --> 00:11:16.155
- Taking off.
- Okay.

00:11:36.634 --> 00:11:38.093
There! The right one.

00:11:38.177 --> 00:11:41.430
- Zero-five-two-five and star.
- Zero-five-two-five, star.

00:11:44.391 --> 00:11:46.352
There. In her room.

00:11:47.978 --> 00:11:49.188
Ji-woo.

00:11:49.271 --> 00:11:51.565
Ji-woo! Wake up.

00:11:57.279 --> 00:11:58.614
What… Where did he go?

00:12:01.450 --> 00:12:02.576
What's going on?

00:12:02.660 --> 00:12:04.286
Did you see a taxi here?

00:12:07.081 --> 00:12:08.874
Did you perhaps drive here?

00:12:35.693 --> 00:12:36.735
Get the doors, please.

00:12:46.537 --> 00:12:48.247
Patient, can you hear me?

00:13:25.659 --> 00:13:26.702
Ji-woo.

00:13:29.830 --> 00:13:30.831
Ji-woo.

00:13:33.292 --> 00:13:35.044
She had acute stomach cramps.

00:13:35.544 --> 00:13:36.712
She's okay now.

00:13:43.344 --> 00:13:44.928
Mom's here.

00:13:51.060 --> 00:13:52.061
I'm sorry.

00:13:52.770 --> 00:13:56.106
I had no idea his past would be an issue.

00:13:56.690 --> 00:14:00.486
Now, the defense will keep
pouncing on Mr. Lee's character.

00:14:01.195 --> 00:14:02.905
To deal with them,

00:14:02.988 --> 00:14:04.615
I need to know about him.

00:14:05.282 --> 00:14:07.493
I mean, everything about him
including his past.

00:14:09.370 --> 00:14:12.247
The first time I met him was 20 years ago.

00:14:13.123 --> 00:14:14.625
Where do I hang it?

00:14:14.708 --> 00:14:16.085
Over here, please.

00:14:16.168 --> 00:14:17.211
- Here?
- Yes.

00:14:17.294 --> 00:14:18.962
I went to Cheongju Prison

00:14:19.046 --> 00:14:21.840
with my church people
to hold a Christmas service there.

00:14:22.549 --> 00:14:25.886
Gang-pung helped me make a Christmas tree.

00:14:28.430 --> 00:14:31.141
He made foolish decisions
and became a gangster,

00:14:31.684 --> 00:14:33.811
but he reflected on his wrongdoings,

00:14:33.894 --> 00:14:36.146
turned himself in, and went to prison.

00:14:42.277 --> 00:14:44.113
{\an8}VICTIM OF MALPRACTICE IN LEGAL BATTLE
WAS ONCE A GANGSTER

00:14:49.910 --> 00:14:51.620
I think that's enough.

00:14:53.247 --> 00:14:54.999
Let's go.

00:14:59.962 --> 00:15:02.339
You should be with Ji-woo for now.

00:15:02.840 --> 00:15:05.634
I'll do what I can
to prepare for the trial.

00:15:05.718 --> 00:15:06.844
Okay.

00:15:06.927 --> 00:15:09.555
- Attorney Shin.
- Yes?

00:15:09.638 --> 00:15:12.266
How did you enter my house, though?

00:15:12.975 --> 00:15:15.477
And how did you know that Ji-woo was sick?

00:15:16.437 --> 00:15:17.479
Oh, that…

00:15:18.313 --> 00:15:21.692
I went there
to get your signature on something

00:15:21.775 --> 00:15:24.236
and found Ji-woo unconscious.

00:15:24.319 --> 00:15:25.320
The door…

00:15:26.447 --> 00:15:28.240
The door was open.

00:15:29.283 --> 00:15:32.536
I wonder why the door was open.

00:15:35.914 --> 00:15:37.041
Then,

00:15:37.124 --> 00:15:40.335
why did you suddenly speak in a dialect
during the trial?

00:15:45.549 --> 00:15:48.343
I'm also from the same darn region.

00:15:49.928 --> 00:15:53.057
I speak in my hometown dialect
when I get worked up.

00:15:55.559 --> 00:15:57.394
Ji-woo shouldn't be alone.

00:15:57.478 --> 00:15:58.812
Hurry inside now.

00:15:58.896 --> 00:16:01.523
Okay, I will.

00:16:01.607 --> 00:16:03.400
- Sure, sure thing.
- Bye.

00:16:06.195 --> 00:16:07.196
Look.

00:16:09.907 --> 00:16:10.908
Thank you.

00:16:10.991 --> 00:16:13.035
It wasn't for you.

00:16:15.579 --> 00:16:18.499
Stay here and join me later
when Ji-woo gets better.

00:16:19.666 --> 00:16:21.001
Let's work on our next plan.

00:16:21.543 --> 00:16:22.544
Okay.

00:16:44.691 --> 00:16:45.692
Attorney Han.

00:16:50.280 --> 00:16:51.281
Attorney Han?

00:16:53.075 --> 00:16:54.076
Hello.

00:16:56.286 --> 00:16:57.621
You didn't leave.

00:16:58.539 --> 00:16:59.540
How is the girl?

00:17:00.415 --> 00:17:03.168
She still has a fever,
but she's stable now.

00:17:05.087 --> 00:17:07.464
You look a little pale.

00:17:08.132 --> 00:17:09.133
Are you okay?

00:17:10.592 --> 00:17:11.593
I'm okay.

00:17:18.142 --> 00:17:19.309
Is she not feeling well?

00:17:46.753 --> 00:17:47.754
Mom, I'm back.

00:17:50.257 --> 00:17:53.093
W-What is it this time? You're scaring me.

00:17:53.177 --> 00:17:54.303
Shin I-rang.

00:18:01.351 --> 00:18:02.769
Look me straight in the eye.

00:18:05.522 --> 00:18:08.192
It's scary every time you call me
by my full name.

00:18:09.443 --> 00:18:11.445
Did I do something wrong again?

00:18:17.910 --> 00:18:18.911
Goodness.

00:18:20.495 --> 00:18:21.830
Mom.

00:18:21.914 --> 00:18:23.624
This is a bit awkward.

00:18:23.707 --> 00:18:26.168
Can't you be on my case as usual?

00:18:26.793 --> 00:18:27.836
No way.

00:18:28.462 --> 00:18:31.423
I can't possibly mistreat my precious son.

00:18:32.007 --> 00:18:35.219
But we should be precise
with calculations.

00:18:39.556 --> 00:18:40.724
Let's see.

00:18:41.642 --> 00:18:43.602
COMMERCIAL LEASE AGREEMENT

00:18:45.437 --> 00:18:46.605
You found out?

00:18:47.105 --> 00:18:48.398
It was too easy.

00:18:48.982 --> 00:18:51.818
You opened a law office under your name.

00:18:51.902 --> 00:18:53.528
It was obvious where you got the money.

00:18:55.405 --> 00:18:57.157
Mom, the thing is--

00:18:57.241 --> 00:18:58.617
It's okay.

00:18:58.700 --> 00:19:02.412
Now that it turned out this way,
I'll consider it an investment.

00:19:03.080 --> 00:19:04.331
Stamp your fingerprint here.

00:19:04.414 --> 00:19:05.415
What…

00:19:05.499 --> 00:19:07.626
HALF OF SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE
BELONGS TO MOM

00:19:07.709 --> 00:19:08.794
Half?

00:19:08.877 --> 00:19:11.630
Sure we're immediate family,
but this isn't fair.

00:19:11.713 --> 00:19:13.173
Should I own it all, then?

00:19:16.093 --> 00:19:17.469
Fine.

00:19:17.552 --> 00:19:19.179
I don't have an ink pad, though.

00:19:29.606 --> 00:19:31.024
MOM: PARK GYEONG-HWA
SON: SHIN I-RANG

00:19:31.108 --> 00:19:32.734
There you go.

00:19:33.777 --> 00:19:36.280
It's nearby, so have your meals here.

00:19:36.780 --> 00:19:37.948
You can drive…

00:19:39.074 --> 00:19:40.200
There's a car?

00:19:44.246 --> 00:19:47.708
{\an8}SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE

00:19:48.625 --> 00:19:49.668
Here you go.

00:19:50.252 --> 00:19:51.461
Its oil needs to be changed.

00:19:52.254 --> 00:19:55.424
PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

00:20:01.138 --> 00:20:05.142
{\an8}PITTER-PATTER BUTCHER-STYLE BBQ

00:20:10.856 --> 00:20:12.899
- Geez, that startled me!
- Oh, my goodness!

00:20:14.860 --> 00:20:16.903
Can't you just show up in an ordinary way?

00:20:16.987 --> 00:20:18.822
I freaked out even more.

00:20:19.573 --> 00:20:20.991
Want me to knock or something?

00:20:21.074 --> 00:20:24.036
To open the door and put the seat belt on?

00:20:24.786 --> 00:20:25.996
Keep your cool, I-rang.

00:20:26.663 --> 00:20:28.165
You're not dealing with a human.

00:20:30.709 --> 00:20:31.793
Anyway,

00:20:32.586 --> 00:20:34.755
shouldn't we find Nurse Oh Jin-suk?

00:20:35.672 --> 00:20:38.175
No one will believe us without her.

00:20:40.093 --> 00:20:41.928
- I found her.
- What?

00:20:42.012 --> 00:20:43.847
I got a call from the detective agency.

00:20:45.599 --> 00:20:48.935
Ms. Oh is a divorced mom
raising her child alone.

00:20:50.145 --> 00:20:53.106
She was so poor that when Lee Jeong-seok
offered money to silence her,

00:20:53.774 --> 00:20:55.025
she couldn't turn it down.

00:20:55.609 --> 00:20:56.818
Nurse Oh Jin-suk?

00:21:10.540 --> 00:21:11.875
A mom can do anything…

00:21:14.669 --> 00:21:15.879
for her child.

00:21:19.758 --> 00:21:20.759
But is that really

00:21:22.469 --> 00:21:23.762
for your child?

00:21:25.972 --> 00:21:26.973
Hi, guys.

00:21:33.522 --> 00:21:34.856
Why? What is it?

00:21:38.193 --> 00:21:39.194
What's going on?

00:21:41.905 --> 00:21:42.906
What is it?

00:21:45.450 --> 00:21:47.411
FOLLOW YOUR DAD TO PRISON
YOUR DAD IS A LIAR

00:21:47.494 --> 00:21:49.454
LEAVE OUR SCHOOL!
DID A GHOST TAKE YOUR DAD?

00:21:55.794 --> 00:21:57.003
I-RANG'S DAD IS A CRIMINAL!

00:21:57.087 --> 00:21:58.463
I know it all too well

00:21:59.464 --> 00:22:01.216
how devastating it is for a child…

00:22:02.175 --> 00:22:03.176
CORRUPT PROSECUTOR

00:22:03.260 --> 00:22:05.470
…when they realize the dirty truth

00:22:06.596 --> 00:22:08.056
behind the privileges they've had.

00:22:08.765 --> 00:22:10.350
That's not the case for Jun-seo.

00:22:13.353 --> 00:22:14.354
He's too young

00:22:15.605 --> 00:22:16.898
to know anything.

00:22:18.817 --> 00:22:19.818
All right.

00:22:20.861 --> 00:22:23.655
Let's say you'll manage
to keep him in the dark somehow.

00:22:24.698 --> 00:22:27.325
- But have you been at ease?
- It's too late now.

00:22:30.370 --> 00:22:32.622
Once you die, you're dead for good.

00:22:33.165 --> 00:22:34.583
It's all over.

00:22:34.666 --> 00:22:35.834
It's not over.

00:22:38.962 --> 00:22:40.463
There's another person dying.

00:22:41.923 --> 00:22:43.258
What do you mean?

00:22:43.842 --> 00:22:45.051
Mr. Lee Gang-pung's daughter.

00:22:46.803 --> 00:22:48.138
You've seen her at the hospital.

00:22:54.227 --> 00:22:55.729
Make it quick and come back out, okay?

00:22:55.812 --> 00:22:57.063
I have an exam tomorrow.

00:22:58.190 --> 00:23:00.817
Take it easy with your exams.

00:23:01.401 --> 00:23:03.195
Stop joking around.

00:23:03.278 --> 00:23:04.905
Okay, my kiddo.

00:23:05.864 --> 00:23:07.699
My surgery will be over in a jiffy.

00:23:08.909 --> 00:23:10.619
Good luck.

00:23:10.702 --> 00:23:11.703
Don't worry.

00:23:14.706 --> 00:23:16.958
- See you.
- See you later.

00:23:19.461 --> 00:23:21.087
Since her dad died,

00:23:21.171 --> 00:23:24.090
she cooped herself in her room
and barely ate anything.

00:23:25.592 --> 00:23:28.553
She ended up passing out
and got sent to the ER.

00:23:33.016 --> 00:23:35.352
Her healthy dad died overnight.

00:23:37.270 --> 00:23:38.271
It'd be odd

00:23:39.606 --> 00:23:40.690
if she were okay.

00:23:46.238 --> 00:23:47.364
Now that you know,

00:23:48.907 --> 00:23:49.908
please testify.

00:23:51.368 --> 00:23:53.912
You're the only one
who can tell the truth.

00:23:55.330 --> 00:23:56.331
So, please…

00:23:58.959 --> 00:24:00.335
reveal the truth.

00:24:04.881 --> 00:24:05.882
I can't do it.

00:24:08.343 --> 00:24:10.679
That man is going to make us pay.

00:24:14.808 --> 00:24:17.936
What else haven't you told me
other than Oh Jin-suk?

00:24:18.895 --> 00:24:22.399
I'm asking if the search and seizure
may find anything against us.

00:24:22.983 --> 00:24:25.652
An EMR, for example.

00:24:25.735 --> 00:24:27.153
EMR…

00:24:27.237 --> 00:24:28.238
What's that?

00:24:28.947 --> 00:24:30.448
Electronic Medical Record.

00:24:30.532 --> 00:24:32.867
It's the mainframe
of a hospital's computer room.

00:24:32.951 --> 00:24:35.203
All surgical records are stored in it.

00:24:36.246 --> 00:24:37.247
Anesthesia doctor?

00:24:37.330 --> 00:24:40.375
Does it mean it has a record
of my heart rate during the surgery?

00:24:40.458 --> 00:24:41.459
That's right.

00:24:41.543 --> 00:24:43.753
Only if we find that hard disk,

00:24:43.837 --> 00:24:46.715
we can perfectly prove
against the doctor's claim

00:24:46.798 --> 00:24:48.508
that you died of a heart attack.

00:24:49.759 --> 00:24:51.803
You should be called Attorney Romantic.

00:24:51.886 --> 00:24:54.389
Did you graduate from med school too?

00:24:54.472 --> 00:24:55.473
What a playlist.

00:24:55.557 --> 00:24:56.891
- What?
- What?

00:24:58.727 --> 00:25:00.103
I didn't know until today.

00:25:00.895 --> 00:25:01.896
Mr. Attorney.

00:25:05.483 --> 00:25:07.319
They submitted
a fabricated record to court.

00:25:09.029 --> 00:25:10.155
Search through the EMR.

00:25:10.989 --> 00:25:13.408
The original should be
in the operating room's computer.

00:25:15.577 --> 00:25:17.370
Ms. Oh Jin-suk told me.

00:25:17.454 --> 00:25:18.913
Oh, I see.

00:25:18.997 --> 00:25:21.207
Anyway, it'll be game over
with that, right?

00:25:22.167 --> 00:25:23.960
But where is it?

00:25:24.044 --> 00:25:25.253
That's the question.

00:25:25.837 --> 00:25:27.339
When I asked the hospital for it,

00:25:27.422 --> 00:25:29.049
they said they recently got a new one.

00:25:29.132 --> 00:25:31.509
They got a new one?
What about the old one, then?

00:25:32.218 --> 00:25:33.219
They sold it.

00:25:33.303 --> 00:25:34.304
Sold it?

00:25:35.055 --> 00:25:37.098
So, I made an anonymous report.

00:25:37.182 --> 00:25:39.184
The prosecution should've
started investigating by now.

00:25:39.267 --> 00:25:41.436
I'll check the surveillance footage
around the hospital.

00:25:41.519 --> 00:25:44.731
I need you to collect information
by the prosecutor in charge.

00:25:45.231 --> 00:25:46.232
Okay.

00:25:49.527 --> 00:25:50.820
From what I heard,

00:25:50.904 --> 00:25:53.782
the prosecution got an anonymous report
about the EMR.

00:25:54.366 --> 00:25:56.284
That's why they started investigating.

00:25:57.035 --> 00:25:59.871
We're about to get busted
thanks to some idiot.

00:25:59.954 --> 00:26:00.955
{\an8}What did you say, woman?

00:26:01.039 --> 00:26:02.999
{\an8}Watch what you say, Attorney Han.

00:26:03.083 --> 00:26:05.710
I can't chime in with improbable lies.

00:26:05.794 --> 00:26:07.879
Are you kidding me?

00:26:07.962 --> 00:26:09.464
- Han Na-hyun.
- Yes?

00:26:09.547 --> 00:26:10.673
You're dismissed.

00:26:12.258 --> 00:26:13.843
I'm in charge of this case.

00:26:15.470 --> 00:26:16.513
You heard me.

00:26:19.224 --> 00:26:22.227
{\an8}TAEBAEK LAW FIRM

00:26:28.316 --> 00:26:30.318
Gosh, I'm lost for words.

00:26:31.444 --> 00:26:32.737
What's with her?

00:26:36.491 --> 00:26:37.575
Geez.

00:26:56.052 --> 00:26:57.095
What…

00:26:57.178 --> 00:26:58.430
What's wrong?

00:27:05.061 --> 00:27:06.146
I understand.

00:27:06.938 --> 00:27:09.107
You killed a man.
No wonder you're losing your mind.

00:27:09.190 --> 00:27:10.191
Kill…

00:27:11.609 --> 00:27:14.446
Kill him? Who do you mean?

00:27:14.529 --> 00:27:17.574
I did speak to you kindly with honorifics,

00:27:18.658 --> 00:27:19.742
but we're not friends.

00:27:19.826 --> 00:27:20.827
Wait.

00:27:21.327 --> 00:27:23.371
I offered that nurse money as you advised.

00:27:23.913 --> 00:27:27.292
I handed over the EMR to you
because you said you'd take care of it.

00:27:29.169 --> 00:27:30.170
I…

00:27:31.504 --> 00:27:33.923
even recorded our conversations,

00:27:35.008 --> 00:27:36.009
sir…

00:27:40.555 --> 00:27:41.556
So what?

00:27:42.474 --> 00:27:43.933
Who's going to listen to it?

00:27:44.934 --> 00:27:46.227
The judges?

00:27:46.895 --> 00:27:49.939
Will you let them know
that you messed up and killed a man,

00:27:50.023 --> 00:27:52.609
and that your attorney helped you
get away with it?

00:27:52.692 --> 00:27:54.611
- No, that's not it.
- Hey!

00:28:02.660 --> 00:28:04.746
When someone cleans up after your mess,

00:28:04.829 --> 00:28:06.331
you should be grateful

00:28:07.665 --> 00:28:10.251
if you ever see reason, okay?

00:28:18.176 --> 00:28:20.595
Consider yourself blessed
to have Attorney Han defend you.

00:28:25.308 --> 00:28:28.102
Han Na-hyun would even risk her life
to win a trial.

00:28:48.164 --> 00:28:49.499
CONTACTS

00:28:49.582 --> 00:28:51.209
PROSECUTOR KIM HYEON-U

00:28:51.292 --> 00:28:52.460
A hospital computer?

00:28:54.462 --> 00:28:56.130
We don't service such computers.

00:28:56.965 --> 00:29:00.718
Then, could there be a place
that services used hospital computers?

00:29:00.802 --> 00:29:01.928
Probably.

00:29:05.014 --> 00:29:06.015
An informant?

00:29:06.850 --> 00:29:09.477
I know you tried
to find this anonymous informant.

00:29:10.353 --> 00:29:12.939
If they're going to testify,
we have the right to know who it is.

00:29:13.022 --> 00:29:14.357
I don't know who it is.

00:29:14.983 --> 00:29:17.777
The person used a public phone,
and no CCTV cameras were nearby.

00:29:20.154 --> 00:29:23.575
Based on the report,
it's highly likely to be an insider.

00:29:23.658 --> 00:29:26.703
Don't you have anyone in mind?
Or maybe the doctor said something.

00:29:27.912 --> 00:29:29.080
No.

00:29:29.163 --> 00:29:32.083
Hospitals are where
random people come and go.

00:29:32.166 --> 00:29:33.918
He said he couldn't specify anyone.

00:29:37.338 --> 00:29:39.173
INVESTIGATOR LEE
I THINK WE FOUND IT

00:29:39.257 --> 00:29:40.550
Just a moment.

00:29:44.971 --> 00:29:46.764
Let me go to the bathroom.

00:29:46.848 --> 00:29:47.849
Sure.

00:30:08.369 --> 00:30:09.537
What's wrong?

00:30:10.747 --> 00:30:11.915
I dropped it in the bathroom.

00:30:13.166 --> 00:30:15.168
I have to make an urgent call.
Can I use your phone?

00:30:15.251 --> 00:30:16.252
Of course.

00:30:30.558 --> 00:30:32.477
"Saenara Used Appliances."

00:30:47.116 --> 00:30:48.326
MR. YANG DO-GYEONG

00:30:49.243 --> 00:30:50.787
Hello, Attorney Yang.

00:30:50.870 --> 00:30:52.413
Did you take care of the computer?

00:30:52.497 --> 00:30:54.707
It will cross the sea

00:30:54.791 --> 00:30:57.377
to meet its new owner tonight.

00:30:57.961 --> 00:30:59.545
Did you get rid of the hard disk?

00:30:59.629 --> 00:31:01.297
Of course, I burned it and threw it out.

00:31:02.048 --> 00:31:04.550
The prosecution is sniffing around.
Be careful.

00:31:04.634 --> 00:31:05.885
Okay, goodbye.

00:31:11.975 --> 00:31:13.434
CHEONGIL HOSPITAL

00:31:13.518 --> 00:31:16.020
I'd be crazy
if I got rid of this nice safety net.

00:31:18.648 --> 00:31:20.900
Let's go to the warehouse.

00:31:28.449 --> 00:31:29.450
Where did you find it?

00:31:30.868 --> 00:31:32.578
We received pictures from our source.

00:31:34.247 --> 00:31:35.873
They were taken last night.

00:31:36.541 --> 00:31:38.793
I asked the hospital,
and they said it was their device.

00:31:39.502 --> 00:31:40.628
Where's the location?

00:31:40.712 --> 00:31:43.006
Incheon, and the owner is Cho Gi-cheol.

00:31:44.674 --> 00:31:45.675
Incheon.

00:31:47.385 --> 00:31:48.761
Should we request a search warrant?

00:31:49.804 --> 00:31:52.056
It'll be too late if we wait for it.
Let's head there now.

00:31:59.355 --> 00:32:00.356
Mr. Attorney.

00:32:01.232 --> 00:32:03.276
Saenara Used Appliances has the computer.

00:32:03.359 --> 00:32:05.486
- Saenara Used Appliances?
- I saw them talking.

00:32:20.418 --> 00:32:22.628
{\an8}KANG HA-NA
SUPREME PROSECUTORS' OFFICE

00:32:29.469 --> 00:32:30.470
{\an8}KIM HAE-YEONG

00:32:30.553 --> 00:32:31.554
{\an8}Attached is the info

00:32:31.637 --> 00:32:33.222
on Saenara Used Appliances and its owner.

00:32:33.306 --> 00:32:34.557
CRIMINAL RECORDS CHECK REPORT

00:32:34.640 --> 00:32:35.808
BUSINESS LICENSE

00:32:42.065 --> 00:32:43.107
Great work today! Thank you!

00:32:47.403 --> 00:32:49.655
You didn't have to come
all the way here, I-rang.

00:32:50.323 --> 00:32:52.533
You know I played a surgeon role

00:32:52.617 --> 00:32:55.161
in the SBS weekend drama,
Doctors, a year ago.

00:32:55.244 --> 00:32:58.915
I didn't have any lines, but I got
quite a lot of blood on my hands.

00:32:58.998 --> 00:33:00.833
Oh, you did.

00:33:01.542 --> 00:33:02.794
I was in a rush.

00:33:03.711 --> 00:33:05.922
Anyway, we need to find
a computer mainframe

00:33:06.005 --> 00:33:08.925
a bit bigger than a normal computer
with a blue sticker on it.

00:33:09.008 --> 00:33:10.968
I see. Don't you worry.
You can count on me.

00:33:11.052 --> 00:33:12.553
- Okay.
- Let's go.

00:33:14.222 --> 00:33:15.223
Off we go.

00:33:30.655 --> 00:33:32.949
SAENARA USED APPLIANCES

00:33:35.326 --> 00:33:36.369
We're here.

00:33:49.382 --> 00:33:50.383
Excuse me…

00:34:04.105 --> 00:34:05.815
What are you going to do with that?

00:34:06.649 --> 00:34:08.442
I doubt any workers are still here.

00:34:08.526 --> 00:34:10.778
- Then?
- I'll just sneak in and get the computer.

00:34:11.904 --> 00:34:14.198
Can you keep watch on that side?

00:34:14.282 --> 00:34:15.199
Okay.

00:34:15.783 --> 00:34:16.909
Hey…

00:34:17.410 --> 00:34:19.036
This makes me feel uneasy.

00:34:29.672 --> 00:34:30.673
Look.

00:34:30.756 --> 00:34:32.175
I think you should be careful.

00:34:32.967 --> 00:34:35.136
I know the owner here.

00:34:35.720 --> 00:34:36.971
You know him?

00:34:37.054 --> 00:34:39.640
He used to be my boss
back when I was young and stupid.

00:34:40.183 --> 00:34:41.851
Are you saying he's a gangster?

00:34:42.768 --> 00:34:43.853
He was vicious.

00:34:44.478 --> 00:34:47.190
He beat up whoever displeased him
to a pulp.

00:34:47.857 --> 00:34:49.942
Every time, he sang the same song.

00:34:52.570 --> 00:34:54.739
A gangster exports used appliances
for a living?

00:34:55.990 --> 00:34:57.950
Maybe he turned over a new leaf.

00:34:58.618 --> 00:35:00.328
Even a dog passing by would laugh.

00:35:03.664 --> 00:35:06.500
He started trafficking drugs 20 years ago.

00:35:06.584 --> 00:35:07.877
What? Drugs?

00:35:16.177 --> 00:35:17.929
Does that mean
this place isn't a warehouse,

00:35:18.012 --> 00:35:19.764
but the den of a drug syndicate?

00:35:21.265 --> 00:35:23.684
Sure seems like it with those guys around.

00:35:24.310 --> 00:35:27.730
- What's going on?
- Who the heck is it?

00:35:28.773 --> 00:35:30.983
You should've told me that sooner!

00:35:31.067 --> 00:35:33.653
Please don't save important information!

00:35:34.237 --> 00:35:36.030
I'd been meaning to tell you.

00:35:36.113 --> 00:35:37.782
I-rang!

00:35:37.865 --> 00:35:40.868
These guys seem very angry!

00:35:41.410 --> 00:35:42.411
Get them!

00:35:42.495 --> 00:35:43.913
What's going on?

00:35:48.292 --> 00:35:49.335
Get them!

00:35:59.095 --> 00:36:00.304
Move over.

00:36:06.477 --> 00:36:07.687
Two people aren't enough.

00:36:09.647 --> 00:36:10.898
- Just a moment.
- What?

00:36:10.982 --> 00:36:13.150
Where are you going, I-rang!

00:36:20.449 --> 00:36:21.659
Help out!

00:36:21.742 --> 00:36:22.994
I'm sorry!

00:36:24.578 --> 00:36:27.164
I-rang, I'm doing what I can!

00:36:27.748 --> 00:36:28.916
I didn't mean you.

00:36:30.001 --> 00:36:31.002
Bong-su, over here.

00:36:48.019 --> 00:36:50.604
I-rang, hold this position.

00:36:50.688 --> 00:36:52.481
I'll go find the computer, okay?

00:36:52.565 --> 00:36:53.858
But…

00:36:54.442 --> 00:36:55.443
Me too!

00:36:56.944 --> 00:37:00.072
So what if you find it?
We have no way out of here!

00:37:13.502 --> 00:37:15.379
You got brains in those heads of yours?

00:37:15.463 --> 00:37:17.798
There are windows on the side!

00:37:17.882 --> 00:37:18.841
- Yes, sir!
- The windows!

00:37:18.924 --> 00:37:19.800
Get the windows.

00:37:19.884 --> 00:37:21.719
Damn morons.

00:37:39.570 --> 00:37:41.572
What are you waiting for?
They're about to come in!

00:37:41.655 --> 00:37:42.907
Oh, here are the computers.

00:37:42.990 --> 00:37:44.700
Hold on. A bit bigger. A blue sticker.

00:37:44.784 --> 00:37:46.410
A bit bigger. A blue sticker.

00:37:47.286 --> 00:37:48.329
Outta my way.

00:37:51.248 --> 00:37:54.585
Gosh. A bit bigger. A blue sticker. A bit…

00:37:58.506 --> 00:37:59.715
A blue sticker.

00:37:59.799 --> 00:38:00.883
I found it!

00:38:04.553 --> 00:38:08.933
I-rang, I found the computer,
but the hard disk is missing!

00:38:09.517 --> 00:38:11.018
It doesn't matter!

00:38:11.852 --> 00:38:13.604
Find a hole in the wall or something!

00:38:34.250 --> 00:38:35.459
I found it!

00:38:35.543 --> 00:38:36.961
I found it here.

00:38:37.044 --> 00:38:38.045
Really?

00:38:44.677 --> 00:38:46.178
Where's the computer?

00:38:47.054 --> 00:38:49.473
Computer? No, I found a dog hole.

00:38:50.891 --> 00:38:52.226
W-What?

00:38:52.977 --> 00:38:54.979
You told me
not to save important information.

00:38:55.855 --> 00:38:58.023
The "what" you found
is the important part!

00:38:58.732 --> 00:39:00.985
You darn dog-hole ghost!

00:39:01.068 --> 00:39:02.778
Darn dog hole?

00:39:07.908 --> 00:39:08.909
I mean a dog hole.

00:39:14.665 --> 00:39:15.875
Where are they?

00:39:15.958 --> 00:39:17.251
Let's go. Hurry.

00:39:51.577 --> 00:39:53.120
I'm from the Prosecutors' Office.

00:39:55.456 --> 00:39:56.499
That woman…

00:39:57.041 --> 00:39:59.251
I hear you're keeping important evidence.

00:39:59.835 --> 00:40:01.629
{\an8}KANG HA-NA
SUPREME PROSECUTORS' OFFICE

00:40:01.712 --> 00:40:04.256
Did you buy that online or what?

00:40:05.841 --> 00:40:08.469
Boys, she claims herself
to be a prosecutor.

00:40:11.263 --> 00:40:12.348
Cho Gi-cheol.

00:40:12.431 --> 00:40:15.434
You were born on February 11, 1979.

00:40:15.518 --> 00:40:17.478
Your hometown is
Sasaeng-dong, Chungcheongnam-do.

00:40:18.187 --> 00:40:20.731
Your mother is dead,
and your father is missing.

00:40:20.814 --> 00:40:23.192
You have seven assault convictions
and two fraud convictions.

00:40:24.902 --> 00:40:26.278
You are beyond saving.

00:40:27.196 --> 00:40:28.197
What's your deal?

00:40:29.532 --> 00:40:31.700
What are you saying?

00:40:33.953 --> 00:40:37.039
What you did just now is
assault and obstruction of justice.

00:40:37.623 --> 00:40:39.458
Add concealing crucial evidence to that,

00:40:40.334 --> 00:40:42.127
and you'll be in the slammer for a while.

00:40:43.295 --> 00:40:45.297
I'm going to pile on
the punishment, you see.

00:40:53.264 --> 00:40:54.557
Fine, I'll let you check.

00:40:57.434 --> 00:40:58.435
Boys, open it up.

00:41:09.113 --> 00:41:10.990
Attorney Han is here to find

00:41:11.907 --> 00:41:13.742
what the doctor hid?

00:41:13.826 --> 00:41:15.452
Isn't she on his side?

00:41:19.665 --> 00:41:21.959
I know. This is strange.

00:41:22.835 --> 00:41:23.836
Wow.

00:41:25.296 --> 00:41:27.089
It's the 1991 Grandeur box-type.

00:41:27.673 --> 00:41:30.551
Wow, it's even got authentic interior.

00:41:31.677 --> 00:41:32.803
This is Cho Gi-cheol's car.

00:41:32.886 --> 00:41:35.264
There's a secret space under the seat.

00:41:36.307 --> 00:41:37.308
A secret space?

00:41:38.142 --> 00:41:39.184
What? What did you say?

00:41:42.271 --> 00:41:44.898
I-rang! What are you doing?

00:41:45.399 --> 00:41:47.234
I-rang, don't do that.

00:41:47.818 --> 00:41:49.028
Oh, geez.

00:41:49.111 --> 00:41:50.654
This is not good.

00:41:50.738 --> 00:41:51.822
What are you doing?

00:41:52.615 --> 00:41:53.616
I found it.

00:41:53.699 --> 00:41:55.284
What on earth?

00:41:55.367 --> 00:41:57.536
How did you know where it was?

00:41:59.455 --> 00:42:01.790
It's a business secret.

00:42:02.583 --> 00:42:04.251
What? You're scaring me.

00:42:04.335 --> 00:42:05.919
Anyway, let's get out of here.

00:42:07.254 --> 00:42:08.380
Hold on.

00:42:15.929 --> 00:42:17.014
Actual drugs.

00:42:46.752 --> 00:42:51.048
Oh, dear. We got caught. What should I do?

00:42:52.174 --> 00:42:53.175
Get her.

00:42:53.258 --> 00:42:54.635
The prosecution knows

00:42:55.386 --> 00:42:56.512
that I'm here.

00:42:56.595 --> 00:42:59.640
I don't care if she's a prosecutor.
Get her.

00:43:25.791 --> 00:43:26.834
What the heck?

00:43:27.584 --> 00:43:28.836
Isn't that my car?

00:43:43.517 --> 00:43:45.477
Attorney Han, are you okay?

00:43:46.478 --> 00:43:47.479
I'm screwed.

00:43:48.063 --> 00:43:49.064
Attorney?

00:43:49.773 --> 00:43:50.774
Not a prosecutor?

00:43:51.734 --> 00:43:53.318
Are you or are you not?

00:43:54.695 --> 00:43:56.864
I-rang!

00:43:58.866 --> 00:44:00.159
What?

00:44:00.743 --> 00:44:03.120
What is this cute trick
you're pulling all together?

00:44:03.662 --> 00:44:04.663
Boys!

00:44:05.831 --> 00:44:07.332
Get them all.

00:44:08.625 --> 00:44:09.668
I-rang.

00:44:27.686 --> 00:44:28.771
Wait.

00:44:31.940 --> 00:44:32.941
Wait a minute!

00:44:36.528 --> 00:44:38.947
Whoever is up there,
I know you're watching!

00:44:39.448 --> 00:44:41.492
Please help me out once more!

00:44:41.575 --> 00:44:44.286
Give me strength just this one last time!

00:44:51.668 --> 00:44:54.338
Why didn't you just set this place on fire

00:44:54.421 --> 00:44:56.590
instead of smashing it all?

00:44:56.673 --> 00:44:57.674
You're really

00:44:59.218 --> 00:45:02.179
making things exhausting!

00:45:02.971 --> 00:45:03.972
Darn.

00:45:04.473 --> 00:45:05.933
Turn the music on.

00:45:06.016 --> 00:45:07.017
Yes, sir.

00:45:21.240 --> 00:45:23.242
Put that thing down before you regret it.

00:45:26.453 --> 00:45:27.454
I don't want to.

00:45:28.497 --> 00:45:31.542
Which one should I beat up first?

00:45:31.625 --> 00:45:34.628
Make a guess

00:45:34.711 --> 00:45:35.712
or not!

00:45:36.255 --> 00:45:37.256
Okay,

00:45:37.756 --> 00:45:38.966
the first target is

00:45:39.758 --> 00:45:40.759
the girl who fooled me.

00:45:44.846 --> 00:45:45.847
Are you okay?

00:45:48.517 --> 00:45:49.768
This is unfair.

00:45:50.936 --> 00:45:52.187
I came here first,

00:45:52.688 --> 00:45:54.314
so I should also take
the beating first, no?

00:45:55.857 --> 00:45:57.818
Is that your wish?

00:45:58.318 --> 00:46:01.655
Punk, your wish is
going to come true today.

00:46:02.906 --> 00:46:05.617
Turn up the volume!

00:46:05.701 --> 00:46:09.037
How disappointing of you!
I hear you're good and kind!

00:46:09.538 --> 00:46:12.165
Why are you sitting back
and watching, huh?

00:46:13.125 --> 00:46:14.126
Oh, come on!

00:46:24.469 --> 00:46:25.470
This song…

00:46:27.598 --> 00:46:30.392
It's a happy moment. Happy days.

00:46:31.184 --> 00:46:33.020
Smile. Smile, you punks.

00:46:34.104 --> 00:46:35.939
It's a happy day!

00:46:37.566 --> 00:46:39.192
When they're faced with someone they hate

00:46:39.276 --> 00:46:41.320
or something that causes rage,

00:46:42.112 --> 00:46:43.655
the possibility of possession increases.

00:47:01.673 --> 00:47:03.300
Oh, your cheeks are burning.

00:47:08.430 --> 00:47:09.514
Are you done swinging?

00:47:10.140 --> 00:47:11.141
Is it my turn now?

00:47:11.892 --> 00:47:14.353
What's this strange sense of déjà vu?

00:47:15.479 --> 00:47:17.439
- Who are you?
- Me?

00:47:19.024 --> 00:47:21.860
I'm gangster attorney, Lee Gang-pung!

00:47:23.403 --> 00:47:24.821
What the heck are you saying?

00:47:26.031 --> 00:47:27.032
Stop joking around.

00:47:27.866 --> 00:47:29.993
They're gangsters,
and they even have drugs.

00:47:31.036 --> 00:47:32.454
Don't worry, my dear.

00:47:33.038 --> 00:47:34.539
I'll save you soon.

00:47:34.623 --> 00:47:35.916
Okay?

00:47:37.751 --> 00:47:39.002
"My dear"?

00:47:39.086 --> 00:47:42.714
We might need a whole hospital
to accommodate you all.

00:47:42.798 --> 00:47:44.800
Or a funeral hall can be another option.

00:47:44.883 --> 00:47:47.678
Why you damn nutjob…

00:47:50.681 --> 00:47:52.015
Trying to catch a fly?

00:48:06.655 --> 00:48:08.573
Where do you think you're going?

00:48:09.741 --> 00:48:11.284
Go on! Attack him!

00:48:14.955 --> 00:48:17.207
What in the world?

00:48:26.883 --> 00:48:28.719
I-rang!

00:48:28.802 --> 00:48:29.845
Wait.

00:48:29.928 --> 00:48:30.929
Don't leave us!

00:48:31.012 --> 00:48:32.097
Oh, no!

00:48:34.725 --> 00:48:36.601
No, that's enough!

00:49:01.793 --> 00:49:03.253
You're dead meat!

00:49:20.061 --> 00:49:21.062
What the…

00:49:23.064 --> 00:49:24.149
Push!

00:49:31.114 --> 00:49:32.282
Darn.

00:49:47.798 --> 00:49:49.382
Attack him. Get in there!

00:50:10.654 --> 00:50:11.947
Spare me!

00:50:20.997 --> 00:50:22.040
I don't want to.

00:50:22.541 --> 00:50:25.502
SAENARA USED APPLIANCES

00:50:44.938 --> 00:50:47.148
I-rang!

00:50:47.691 --> 00:50:50.193
What… Can you stay with him?

00:50:50.277 --> 00:50:51.486
I'll go bring people.

00:50:54.322 --> 00:50:55.323
Mr. Shin.

00:50:55.907 --> 00:50:58.285
Attorney Shin, can you hear me?

00:50:58.952 --> 00:50:59.953
Attorney Shin!

00:51:07.544 --> 00:51:09.921
{\an8}CHEONGIL HOSPITAL

00:51:32.569 --> 00:51:34.195
Attorney Han, are you okay?

00:51:47.959 --> 00:51:48.960
Are you okay?

00:51:50.921 --> 00:51:51.963
This is unfair.

00:51:53.131 --> 00:51:54.799
I came here first,

00:51:54.883 --> 00:51:56.718
so I should also take
the beating first, no?

00:52:11.024 --> 00:52:12.275
- Let's go inside.
- Yes, sir.

00:52:12.776 --> 00:52:14.444
Get the nearby surveillance footage first.

00:52:14.527 --> 00:52:15.528
Yes, sir.

00:52:18.615 --> 00:52:22.285
The man who was recently criticized
for playing the victim

00:52:22.369 --> 00:52:25.872
turns out to have been murdered
by the doctor in charge.

00:52:25.956 --> 00:52:29.125
{\an8}The police have proved the doctor's murder

00:52:29.209 --> 00:52:32.087
based on the hospital computer's hard disk

00:52:32.170 --> 00:52:34.839
and the testimony
of the nurse who witnessed it.

00:52:34.923 --> 00:52:35.924
Meanwhile, they're--

00:52:54.693 --> 00:52:58.697
HAN SO-HYUN

00:53:01.783 --> 00:53:04.703
COURT OF KOREA

00:53:08.081 --> 00:53:09.082
EFFORT ALWAYS PAYS OFF

00:53:09.165 --> 00:53:10.583
ATTORNEY SEO IN-GYU DUBBED "KING"

00:53:16.464 --> 00:53:18.299
{\an8}A LAWYER THAT PEOPLE WANT TO EMPLOY!
A LAWYER THAT PEOPLE BELIEVE IN!

00:53:18.383 --> 00:53:19.592
{\an8}I WANT TO BE A LAWYER
THAT ALWAYS WINS!

00:53:19.676 --> 00:53:20.719
I MUST WIN EVERY TIME!

00:53:25.849 --> 00:53:26.850
WON
WON

00:53:27.434 --> 00:53:29.644
{\an8}WON, WON, WON,
WON, WON, WON

00:53:32.772 --> 00:53:35.525
{\an8}WON, WON, WON,
WON, WON, WON

00:54:06.639 --> 00:54:11.061
{\an8}LOST

00:54:12.312 --> 00:54:13.521
- Mr. Attorney.
- Hello.

00:54:22.322 --> 00:54:23.364
How is Ji-woo?

00:54:47.764 --> 00:54:49.015
Hi, Ji-woo.

00:54:50.642 --> 00:54:52.560
I'm Attorney Shin I-rang.

00:54:53.520 --> 00:54:56.523
We met briefly at the hospital, remember?

00:55:00.485 --> 00:55:01.486
Is it still…

00:55:03.029 --> 00:55:04.489
too hard for you?

00:55:17.377 --> 00:55:18.378
Ji-woo.

00:55:20.547 --> 00:55:21.756
Your dad…

00:55:24.050 --> 00:55:26.010
didn't die because of you.

00:55:27.971 --> 00:55:29.722
It's not your fault.

00:55:31.474 --> 00:55:34.102
So, don't blame yourself too much.

00:55:36.646 --> 00:55:38.606
What do you know, mister?

00:55:45.321 --> 00:55:46.322
I…

00:55:48.324 --> 00:55:49.701
can tell.

00:55:53.246 --> 00:55:54.747
What? You don't like it?

00:55:54.831 --> 00:55:56.666
Why are you picking at the food?

00:55:57.292 --> 00:55:58.459
It's nothing.

00:55:58.543 --> 00:56:01.212
No way. I can tell there's something.

00:56:01.713 --> 00:56:03.173
Come on and tell me.

00:56:03.756 --> 00:56:05.884
I couldn't sleep
because you snored too loudly.

00:56:06.467 --> 00:56:07.468
That's not good.

00:56:07.969 --> 00:56:11.181
My kiddo will have trouble getting tall
and studying if she can't sleep.

00:56:11.264 --> 00:56:14.350
This won't do.
I'll go see a doctor right away.

00:56:15.560 --> 00:56:17.103
It's all my fault.

00:56:19.647 --> 00:56:21.691
I heard snoring wasn't good
for your health,

00:56:23.276 --> 00:56:26.321
and I knew my dad
would do anything for me.

00:56:28.281 --> 00:56:30.575
If I just didn't say that,

00:56:31.826 --> 00:56:33.620
he wouldn't have died.

00:56:37.290 --> 00:56:38.583
No, Ji-woo.

00:56:41.419 --> 00:56:42.837
My death…

00:56:44.839 --> 00:56:46.799
is absolutely not your fault.

00:56:48.134 --> 00:56:49.969
The hospital and the doctor are to blame.

00:56:50.720 --> 00:56:54.182
Those in the wrong were all punished.

00:56:54.265 --> 00:56:55.266
So…

00:56:58.353 --> 00:56:59.812
So Ji-woo, please…

00:57:01.731 --> 00:57:02.732
go back

00:57:04.234 --> 00:57:05.610
to your usual bright self.

00:57:07.779 --> 00:57:09.072
Live happily…

00:57:11.074 --> 00:57:13.493
with your mom for me, okay?

00:57:15.954 --> 00:57:17.121
Okay, kiddo?

00:57:20.750 --> 00:57:21.751
Dad?

00:57:43.231 --> 00:57:44.232
Mom.

00:57:45.483 --> 00:57:47.151
I heard Dad's voice.

00:57:47.235 --> 00:57:48.236
What?

00:57:50.697 --> 00:57:54.367
I guess your dad is
always keeping by our side.

00:57:59.330 --> 00:58:02.750
Let's be brave

00:58:02.834 --> 00:58:05.128
and live happily, okay?

00:58:40.204 --> 00:58:41.247
Wait.

00:58:43.333 --> 00:58:46.252
Must we burn this talisman?

00:58:50.131 --> 00:58:52.634
He can just stay with us.

00:58:52.717 --> 00:58:56.137
He'll get to watch Ji-woo grow
and be of support to Min-ju.

00:58:56.220 --> 00:58:57.221
Attorney Shin.

00:58:57.305 --> 00:58:58.765
Why must he go?

00:58:59.515 --> 00:59:00.600
I should.

00:59:01.726 --> 00:59:03.519
I don't belong here.

00:59:11.277 --> 00:59:14.113
Thank you so much for everything.

00:59:21.371 --> 00:59:22.413
The pleasure is mine.

00:59:24.457 --> 00:59:25.458
Thank you.

00:59:29.962 --> 00:59:31.464
It was only for a short time,

00:59:33.049 --> 00:59:34.300
but I was happy.

00:59:36.719 --> 00:59:37.970
I guarantee

00:59:39.430 --> 00:59:41.683
you'll go to a good place.

00:59:45.061 --> 00:59:46.104
Farewell.

01:01:36.047 --> 01:01:39.050
OKCHEON BUILDING

01:01:44.096 --> 01:01:46.015
- Is it all over?
- Yes.

01:01:46.098 --> 01:01:48.768
Your son is inside. Go on ahead.

01:01:49.477 --> 01:01:50.853
Father.

01:01:50.937 --> 01:01:51.938
Yes?

01:01:52.021 --> 01:01:54.065
Thank you so much.

01:01:54.899 --> 01:01:55.900
Don't mention it.

01:01:57.068 --> 01:01:58.069
Goodbye.

01:02:06.369 --> 01:02:09.372
{\an8}JOB APPLICATION
NAME: SHIN I-RANG

01:02:14.210 --> 01:02:15.419
Are you busy?

01:02:17.588 --> 01:02:18.923
What brings you here, Mom?

01:02:20.508 --> 01:02:24.887
I'm here to feed my attorney son
who's working late hours.

01:02:29.725 --> 01:02:30.726
Mom,

01:02:31.310 --> 01:02:33.020
about Dad…

01:02:36.440 --> 01:02:37.441
What about him?

01:02:40.528 --> 01:02:42.238
Never mind.

01:02:43.698 --> 01:02:44.699
What is it?

01:02:48.452 --> 01:02:49.453
You know,

01:02:50.204 --> 01:02:52.331
when we arrived at the hospital,

01:02:53.749 --> 01:02:55.543
he was already dead.

01:02:57.962 --> 01:02:59.255
I'm wondering

01:03:00.172 --> 01:03:02.383
if he wanted to tell us anything.

01:03:04.552 --> 01:03:06.053
If he did,

01:03:07.805 --> 01:03:11.684
he might show up to us at least once.

01:03:15.646 --> 01:03:16.981
Nonsense.

01:03:22.528 --> 01:03:23.529
Well,

01:03:24.363 --> 01:03:26.449
I guess it wouldn't be so bad
if he did show up.

01:03:29.076 --> 01:03:32.079
I have tons of questions for him too.

01:03:38.377 --> 01:03:39.879
Eat up before it gets cold.

01:03:39.962 --> 01:03:41.213
Don't be home too late.

01:03:41.923 --> 01:03:42.924
See you.

01:03:43.466 --> 01:03:44.508
You're leaving already?

01:05:10.636 --> 01:05:11.637
That's right.

01:05:12.388 --> 01:05:14.932
Let's say the worst is behind us now

01:05:15.016 --> 01:05:16.434
and make a fresh start.

01:05:22.273 --> 01:05:23.524
This should be enough

01:05:23.607 --> 01:05:26.861
to ward off even the oldest ghosts.

01:05:28.696 --> 01:05:30.114
{\an8}LEGAL CONSULTATION, LEGAL ADVICE
SHIN I-RANG LAW OFFICE

01:06:16.827 --> 01:06:19.121
How may I help you, girl?

01:06:24.168 --> 01:06:26.253
What brings you here?

01:06:31.634 --> 01:06:33.135
Mister,

01:06:34.136 --> 01:06:35.429
you can see me?

01:06:36.055 --> 01:06:37.056
What?

01:06:52.446 --> 01:06:53.447
Not again.

01:06:55.116 --> 01:06:57.868
Why does it keep happening to me?

01:07:36.615 --> 01:07:39.493
{\an8}You looked so cool
when you were dancing earlier.

01:07:39.577 --> 01:07:42.246
{\an8}A trainee committed suicide
and the fans are going wild.

01:07:42.329 --> 01:07:43.622
{\an8}Let me look into it.

01:07:43.706 --> 01:07:44.874
{\an8}- Loanne was…
- Hey!

01:07:44.957 --> 01:07:46.959
{\an8}Stop causing harm to others
and just go home.

01:07:47.042 --> 01:07:49.628
{\an8}The girls found it hard to deal with her.

01:07:49.712 --> 01:07:51.213
{\an8}Her phone disappeared from the scene.

01:07:51.297 --> 01:07:52.631
{\an8}You think she was murdered?

01:07:52.715 --> 01:07:54.216
{\an8}Let's go catch the culprit.

01:07:54.300 --> 01:07:55.342
{\an8}Do you know who Loanne is?

01:07:55.426 --> 01:07:56.927
{\an8}- Who are you?
- Who are you? A reporter?

01:07:57.011 --> 01:07:58.804
{\an8}How did you get in? Let's go.

01:07:58.888 --> 01:08:00.431
{\an8}I heard a phone ring.

01:08:02.308 --> 01:08:04.101
{\an8}I never heard that ringtone before.

01:08:04.185 --> 01:08:09.190
{\an8}Subtitle translation by: Eunjin Erica Kim